I have ta simple ES6 module export and VS Code is seeing it as an error:

> Parsing error: Illegal import declaration (undefined)

Yet that is valid, and works just fine. 
Below is the entirety of the module:

```
export class ErrorEvent {
    constructor(structuredError) {
        this.structuredError = structuredError;
    }
}
```

The "export" keyword get's a red squiggly line and an error is added to VS Error error list for it.

Can this please be fixed?
